# Resend notification templates

When you **create or update** any file under `apps/backend/src/notifications/templates/` (HTML email sources), sync that template to Resend so production sends use the latest version and `resend-template-ids.json` stays correct.

## Command

From the **repository root**, with `RESEND_API_KEY` set in the environment:

```bash
npm run sync:resend-template -- en/<template_name>.html
```

Examples:

- One locale: `npm run sync:resend-template -- en/client_rental_request_accepted.html`
- French only: `npm run sync:resend-template -- fr/client_rental_request_accepted.html`
- Both `en/` and `fr/` copies of the same filename: `npm run sync:resend-template -- client_rental_request_accepted.html`

Use `npm run sync:resend-templates` (no extra args) only when a full sync of every template is intentional.

Do not skip the sync after template changes unless the user explicitly says not to or lacks API access.
